ype\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting code behavior**\\n\\nI want to make sure to check if the write operation can throw an exception. It seems like there might be an issue with some unused arguments in the NullWritable close function. I should inspect the source code to clarify this, but I'm not sure if using javap will help. Passing null might be acceptable since it seems the close function may ignore the context. It might be good to analyze existing test methods before I make any edits.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AxO1VUVv79XnG4t3BTfyLeRD|fc_016ef84d30dfe2380169fe4a036a48819f9312aebc30022785", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.avro/avro-mapred/1.10.2/src/test/java/org_apache_avro/avro_mapred/Avro_mapredTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.avro.Schema;\nimport org.apache.avro.file.CodecFactory;", "newText": "import org.apache.avro.Schema;\nimport org.apache.avro.file.CodecFactory;\nimport org.apache.avro.file.DataFileStream;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.avro.hadoop.io.AvroSequenceFile;\nimport org.apache.avro.hadoop.util.AvroCharSequenceComparator;", "newText": "import org.apache.avro.hadoop.io.AvroSequenceFile;\nimport org.apache.avro.hadoop.util.AvroCharSequenceComparator;\nimport org.apache.avro.io.DatumReader;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.avro.mapred.Pair;\nimport org.apache.avro.reflect.ReflectData;", "newText": "import org.apache.avro.mapred.Pair;\nimport org.apache.avro.mapreduce.AvroKeyValueRecordWriter;\nimport org.apache.avro.reflect.ReflectData;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.avro.util.Utf8;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration;", "newText": "import org.apache.avro.util.Utf8;\nimport org.apache.avro.generic.GenericDatumReader;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void charSequenceComparatorOrdersDifferentCharSequenceImplementations() {\n        AvroCharSequenceComparator<CharSequence> comparator = new AvroCharSequenceComparator<>();\n\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(\"alpha\", new Utf8(\"beta\"))).isLessThan(0);\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(new Utf8(\"beta\"), \"alpha\")).isGreaterThan(0);\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(new Utf8(\"same\"), new StringBuilder(\"same\"))).isZero();\n        assertThat(AvroCharSequenceComparator.INSTANCE.compare(\"a\", \"b\")).isLessThan(0);\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void avroKeyValueRecordWriterCreatesReadableAvroDataFiles() throws IOException {\n        Configuration conf = hadoopConfiguration();\n        AvroDatumConverterFactory factory = new AvroDatumConverterFactory(conf);\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        AvroKeyValueRecordWriter<Text, IntWritable> writer = new AvroKeyValueRecordWriter<>(\n                factory.create(Text.class),\n                factory.create(IntWritable.class),\n                GenericData.get(),\n                CodecFactory.nullCodec(),\n                output);\n\n        Schema expectedSchema = AvroKeyValue.getSchema(STRING_SCHEMA, INT_SCHEMA);\n        assertThat(writer.getWriterSchema()).isEqualTo(expectedSchema);\n        writer.write(new Text(\"red\"), new IntWritable(1));\n        long syncPosition = writer.sync();\n        writer.write(new Text(\"green\"), new IntWritable(2));\n        writer.close(null);\n\n        assertThat(syncPosition).isPositive();\n        DatumReader<GenericRecord> datumReader = new GenericDatumReader<>();\n        try (DataFileStream<GenericRecord> reader = new DataFileStream<>(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(output.toByteArray()),\n                datumReader)) {\n            assertThat(reader.getSchema()).isEqualTo(expectedSchema);\n            assertNextKeyValueEntry(reader, \"red\", 1);\n            assertNextKeyValueEntry(reader, \"green\", 2);\n            assertThat(reader.hasNext()).isFalse();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void charSequenceComparatorOrdersDifferentCharSequenceImplementations() {\n        AvroCharSequenceComparator<CharSequence> comparator = new AvroCharSequenceComparator<>();\n\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(\"alpha\", new Utf8(\"beta\"))).isLessThan(0);\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(new Utf8(\"beta\"), \"alpha\")).isGreaterThan(0);\n        assertThat(comparator.compare(new Utf8(\"same\"), new StringBuilder(\"same\"))).isZero();\n        assertThat(AvroCharSequenceComparator.INSTANCE.compare(\"a\", \"b\")).isLessThan(0);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1370, "output": 1902, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30920, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778272752776, "responseId": "resp_016ef84d30dfe2380169fe49f165d8819f8f2a3682bf1810b5"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_AxO1VUVv79XnG4t3BTfyLeRD|fc_016ef84d30dfe2380169fe4a036a48819f9312aebc30022785", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 6 block(s) in tests/src/org.apache.avro/avro-mapred/1.10.2/src/test/java/org_apache_avro/avro_mapred/Avro_mapredTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   5  * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n   6  */\n   7 package org_apache_avro.avro_mapred;\n   8 \n+  9 import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\n+ 10 import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\n   9 import java.io.IOException;\n  10 import java.nio.ByteBuffer;\n  11 import java.util.ArrayList;\n  12 import java.util.List;\n  13 \n  14 import org.apache.avro.Schema;\n  15 import org.apache.avro.file.CodecFactory;\n+ 18 import org.apache.avro.file.DataFileStream;\n  16 import org.apache.avro.generic.Gen